Highlights: Interesting China Doll outro

Fall '84 N10 Excellent, relatively rare SBD from Oct. '84. Stranger opener sets the mood from the start. Especially digging on the Garcia tunes. But it's all well-played and engaged.  Good Dancin' opener. Reworked of course from its late '70s variant. Big Playin' sandwich in the second set. I feel like there's imaginative work in every Playin' from this tour. These China Dolls haunt me. Baby Blue encores.

Gordon's review worked! Been revisiting this fall 84 east coast tour... sounds better than I would have thought in comparison to 72-77 I have been mostly enjoying. 
The Baby Blue sounds good, Jerry's voice is breaking, as it was since Augusta, (could say "since Hampton!") but the playing and the vocal moments work! only into Baby Blue... to start! Looking forward to the rest as time allows! 84 was my first heavy touring year... a buddy and I split a couple of tour packages (mail order) he did some of the early one, I did some of the later ones, we did some together, and some we couldn't make... but overall the trips were worth it! I still think that is the case!
